[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7157,
        "end_time": 10295,
        "text": "Gravity. It controls the universe."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 10295,
        "end_time": 12925,
        "text": "Everything attracts everything else."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 12925,
        "end_time": 13590,
        "text": "Ouch!"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 13590,
        "end_time": 14408,
        "text": "Including you."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 14408,
        "end_time": 15224,
        "text": "Ow!"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 15224,
        "end_time": 16815,
        "text": "In this final lesson,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 16815,
        "end_time": 19699,
        "text": "we&#39;ll explore what gravity means for space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 19699,
        "end_time": 23235,
        "text": "or rather what space-time means for gravity."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 23235,
        "end_time": 25332,
        "text": "Until now, we&#39;ve been dealing with things moving"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 25332,
        "end_time": 27003,
        "text": "at constant speeds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 27003,
        "end_time": 29523,
        "text": "with straight world lines in space-time."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 29523,
        "end_time": 31395,
        "text": "But once you add gravity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 31395,
        "end_time": 33300,
        "text": "if you measure a speed at one moment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 33300,
        "end_time": 34964,
        "text": "then again a bit later,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 34964,
        "end_time": 37086,
        "text": "the speed may have changed."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 37086,
        "end_time": 39079,
        "text": "In other words, as I discovered,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 39079,
        "end_time": 41949,
        "text": "gravity causes acceleration,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 41949,
        "end_time": 43670,
        "text": "so we need the world line to look different"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 43670,
        "end_time": 45375,
        "text": "from one moment to the next."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 45375,
        "end_time": 46890,
        "text": "As we saw in the last lesson,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 46890,
        "end_time": 50101,
        "text": "the correct way to tilt an object&#39;s world line"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 50101,
        "end_time": 52873,
        "text": "is using a Lorentz transformation:"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 52873,
        "end_time": 55365,
        "text": "Einstein&#39;s stretch and squash trick."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 55365,
        "end_time": 58132,
        "text": "So, to map out what gravity is doing to Tom&#39;s motion,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 58132,
        "end_time": 61149,
        "text": "we need to create a whole load of little patches of space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 61149,
        "end_time": 64058,
        "text": "each transformed by different amounts."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 64058,
        "end_time": 66524,
        "text": "So that my world line is at a different angle in each one."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 66524,
        "end_time": 70951,
        "text": "And then, we&#39;re ready to stitch everything together."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 70951,
        "end_time": 73541,
        "text": "We assemble a cozy quilt of space-time"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 73541,
        "end_time": 75942,
        "text": "where world lines look curved."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 75942,
        "end_time": 78940,
        "text": "Where the world lines join, the objects collide."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 78940,
        "end_time": 81873,
        "text": "By making these connections between the patches,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 81873,
        "end_time": 86708,
        "text": "a curvature gets built into space-time itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 86708,
        "end_time": 88616,
        "text": "But Einstein&#39;s true genius"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 88616,
        "end_time": 91485,
        "text": "was to describe precisely how each patch"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 91485,
        "end_time": 92912,
        "text": "is stretched and squashed"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 92912,
        "end_time": 96130,
        "text": "according to nearby mass and energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 96130,
        "end_time": 100424,
        "text": "The mere presence of stuff curves the space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 100424,
        "end_time": 104472,
        "text": "and curving space-time moves the stuff around."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 104472,
        "end_time": 107543,
        "text": "This is gravity, according to Einstein."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 107543,
        "end_time": 111441,
        "text": "Previously, Isaac Newton had explained gravity"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 111441,
        "end_time": 114504,
        "text": "using the ideas of force and acceleration,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 114504,
        "end_time": 116314,
        "text": "without any wibbily wobbly space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 116314,
        "end_time": 117759,
        "text": "and that did pretty well."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 117759,
        "end_time": 120898,
        "text": "But Einstein&#39;s theory does just slightly better"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 120898,
        "end_time": 122432,
        "text": "at predicting, for example,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 122432,
        "end_time": 124291,
        "text": "the orbit of Mercury around the Sun,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 124291,
        "end_time": 127591,
        "text": "or the way that light rays are deflected by massive objects."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 127591,
        "end_time": 130486,
        "text": "More importantly, Einstein&#39;s theory predicts things"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 130486,
        "end_time": 133454,
        "text": "that simply don&#39;t exist in older theories"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 133454,
        "end_time": 136526,
        "text": "where space, time and gravity were separate."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 136526,
        "end_time": 140871,
        "text": "The stitching can leave wrinkles in the space-time material."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 140871,
        "end_time": 143706,
        "text": "These are called gravitational waves,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 143706,
        "end_time": 146465,
        "text": "which should be detectable as tiny, repetitive,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 146465,
        "end_time": 149029,
        "text": "subtle squashes and stretches in space."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 149029,
        "end_time": 152329,
        "text": "So we&#39;re building experiments to check if they are there."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 152329,
        "end_time": 154856,
        "text": "In the meantime, indirect evidence,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 154856,
        "end_time": 157383,
        "text": "most recently in the polarization patterns of light"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 157383,
        "end_time": 159087,
        "text": "left over from the Big Bang,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 159087,
        "end_time": 162352,
        "text": "strongly suggest that they are."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 162352,
        "end_time": 164237,
        "text": "But despite Einstein&#39;s successes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 164237,
        "end_time": 166574,
        "text": "when too much stuff gets concentrated"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 166574,
        "end_time": 168018,
        "text": "in too small a space,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 168018,
        "end_time": 170328,
        "text": "like in a black hole,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 170328,
        "end_time": 172951,
        "text": "the curvature of space-time becomes so large,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 172951,
        "end_time": 178152,
        "text": "that his equations collapse."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 178152,
        "end_time": 180086,
        "text": "We need a new picture of space-time"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 180086,
        "end_time": 182472,
        "text": "that incorporates quantum mechanics"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 182472,
        "end_time": 186029,
        "text": "to unlock the secret at the heart of black holes."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 186029,
        "end_time": 188276,
        "text": "Which means there&#39;s plenty more to be discovered"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 188276,
        "end_time": 192218,
        "text": "about space, time, and space-time in the future."
    }
]